159
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:53,200
So, and well, she was talking about how they perform a manicure and she talked about four
那么，嗯，她在谈论她们如何做美甲时，提到了四

160
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:55,280
coats of nail polish.
层指甲油。

161
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:58,440
So a coat, we know that it's kind of like a jacket, right?
所以“coat”，我们知道它有点像外套，对吧？

162
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:01,320
But in this case, it means a layer.
但在这里，它指的是“层”。

163
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:03,520
So you paint your nails one time.
所以你涂一次指甲。

164
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:04,520
Okay.
好的。

165
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:05,720
You have color.
你有了颜色。

166
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:06,720
Maybe it doesn't look right.
可能看起来不对。

167
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:07,720
Okay.
好的。

168
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:08,720
It's very thin.
它很薄。

169
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:13,280
So you say, okay, I'm going to paint two coats and then you paint one more time and the color
所以你说：好的，我要涂两层，然后你再涂一次，颜色

170
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:17,520
gets darker and you paint one more time and the color gets very dark and very thick.
变深，你再涂一次，颜色变得很深很厚。

171
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:18,800
And so these are called coats.
这些就叫“coats”。

172
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,560
That means layers of nail polish.
意思是指甲油的层数。

173
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:24,080
And that's a special word we use when we're talking about painting our nails.
这是我们在谈论涂指甲时用的一个特殊词。

174
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:25,080
Right.
对。

175
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:28,760
So not only for nails, but if you're painting your house, maybe you need two or three coats
所以不仅是指甲，如果你在粉刷房子，你可能需要两到三层

176
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:29,760
of paint.
油漆。

177
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:30,760
Exactly.
没错。

178
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:35,880
If we have a red wall and we want to paint it white, we definitely need two, three, maybe
如果我们有一面红墙，想把它刷成白色，我们肯定需要两、三，也许

179
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:37,440
four coats of paint.
四层油漆。

180
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:39,200
Otherwise, we'll still see the red.
否则，我们还会看到红色。

181
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,200
Okay.
好的。

182
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,200
Very good.
非常好。

183
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,400
Very interesting phrases.
非常有趣的短语。

184
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:47,640
Let's take a look at this dialogue for the very last time and we'll be back shortly.
让我们最后一次看看这个对话，我们马上回来。

185
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:55,040
Honey, I'll be right back.
亲爱的，我马上回来。

186
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:56,040
Where are you going?
你去哪儿？

187
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:57,520
I told you already.
我已经告诉过你了。

188
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:59,920
I'm going to get my nails done again.
我又要去美甲了。

189
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:01,840
You just went last week.
你上周刚去过。

190
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:05,440
You spend more time at the nail salon than you do here at home.
你在美甲沙龙花的时间比在家还多。

191
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:08,240
Honestly, why do you need a manicure every week?
说实话，你为什么每周都需要做美甲？

192
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:12,560
Well, first of all, I like to pamper myself and my nails look great.
嗯，首先，我喜欢宠自己，而且我的指甲看起来很棒。

193
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:13,560
You should come with me.
你应该跟我一起来。

194
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:14,560
Why?
为什么？

195
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:17,800
I don't want to have nail polish or anything like that.
我不想涂指甲油或做那些东西。

196
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:19,400
They don't only paint my nails.
他们不只是给我涂指甲。

197
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:23,480
The manicurist will remove my cuticles, file my nails and apply at least four coats of
美甲师会帮我修剪死皮、锉指甲，然后至少涂四层

198
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:24,480
nail polish.
指甲油。

199
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:28,480
Yeah, sounds like something I should definitely do.
是啊，听起来确实是我该做的事。

200
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:32,800
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

201
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:38,080
So, Catherine, are you a big fan of manicures?
那么，凯瑟琳，你是美甲的忠实粉丝吗？

202
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:39,400
Do you get it done often?
你经常做吗？

203
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:41,680
I didn't used to, but I really enjoy them now.
我以前不常做，但现在真的很喜欢。

204
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:44,200
I think it's a nice way to relax on the weekends.
我觉得这是周末放松的好方式。

205
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:50,680
So every couple of weeks, I go to the nail salon and I get my nails done.
所以每隔几周，我就去美甲沙龙做美甲。

206
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:51,680
All right.
好的。

207
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:57,040
I think one of the words that we didn't talk about here, but it's very, I don't know, for
我觉得我们这里没提到的一个词，但非常，怎么说呢，对

208
00:09:57,040 --> 00:10:01,640
men it's kind of a strange smell, is nail polish remover.
男人来说味道有点奇怪，是指甲油去除剂。

209
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:03,760
The acetone, right?
丙酮，对吧？

210
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:05,300
It's a very strong chemical.
它是一种很强的化学物质。

211
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:07,280
It is really disgusting.
真的很恶心。

212
00:10:07,280 --> 00:10:11,520
Nail polish remover, you know, the word to remove means to take away.
指甲油去除剂，你知道，“remove”这个词意思是去掉。

213
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:15,280
And so when the nail polish, we want to change the color, we have to use this.
所以当我们想换指甲油颜色时，就得用这个。

214
00:10:15,280 --> 00:10:17,920
It's like water, but it smells really bad.
它像水一样，但味道很难闻。

215
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:22,120
And so my boyfriend always gets angry when I use the nail polish remover because the
所以我男朋友在我用指甲油去除剂时总是生气，因为

216
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:24,760
whole house starts to stink.
整个房子都开始发臭。

217
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:27,040
It's a very strong smell and you get kind of dizzy.
味道很浓，你会有点头晕。

218
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:28,040
So that's why.
所以这就是原因。

219
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:29,040
Yeah, it goes into your head.
是啊，它会冲进你的脑袋。

220
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:30,040
All right.
好的。

221
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:33,560
Well, if you guys have any questions, any doubts, or any suggestions about this lesson
嗯，如果你们对这节课有任何问题、疑问或建议，

222
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:38,480
or any other lesson, please come to our website, EnglishPod.com and we'll see you guys there.
或者任何其他课程，请访问我们的网站 EnglishPod.com，我们会在那里见。

223
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:39,480
Bye, everyone.
大家再见。

224
